Perform final cleaning of data

Source: R/final_clean.R
final_clean.Rd

The final_clean() function performs final cleaning steps, including: removing duplicate data points, checking locality precision, and retaining only one collection point. This function also provides the option to interactively inspect and remove types of basis of record.

Usage

final_clean(df, cluster = TRUE, precision = 2, recordBasis = TRUE)

Arguments

df

Data frame of occurrence records.

cluster

An option (TRUE/FALSE) to cluster geographically close occurrence records. This option is turned on by default.

precision

An option to round coordinates to the specified number of digits. This option is set to 2 by default. To not use any rounding, choose precision = NA.

recordBasis

An option (TRUE/FALSE) to interactively remove types of basis of record. This option is turned on by default.

Value

df is a data frame with the cleaned data.

Details

This function requires packages dplyr, magrittr, raster, and dismo.
